Requirements : 1) Download selenium and import webdriver (Installation guide- https://pypi.org/project/selenium/#description , https://selenium-python.readthedocs.io/waits.html
               2) Should have browser (chrome, firefox)
Steps :
        1) should import webdriver from selenium
        2) Allow user to input the twitter handle
        3) Call the webdriver depending on the browser
        4) Tell the webdriver the time to wait before sending a "No such Element Exception"
        5) direct the twitter using get() method
        6) opens the browser based on the twitter handle displaying the profile
        7) print the number of followers then closes the chrome openned
        8) method to close & destroy both the WebDriver and Web Browser instances gracefully after each run of Test Execution.
